Let $\overline{CH}$  be an altitude of $\triangle ABC$. Applying the Pythagorean Theorem to $\triangle CHB$ and to $\triangle CHD$ produces \[
8^2 - (BD +1)^2 = CH^2 = 7^2 - 1^2 = 48, \quad \text{so} \quad (BD+1)^2 = 16.
\] Thus $BD = \boxed{3}$.

